IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: The mission of the FSW Foundation is to support the strategic priorities of Florida SouthWestern State College by providing additional funding and resources.
IRS990.MissionDesc: The mission of the FSW Foundation is to support the strategic priorities of Florida SouthWestern State College by providing additional funding and resources.
IRS990.Desc: Provided almost $2 million in scholarship support to students of Florida SouthWestern State College. Provided program support funding of almost $1.25 million to support a wide range of FSW Colleges programs, athletics and priorities. Over 20,000 students, faculty and staff were positively impacted. The Foundation continued to cultivate the community resulting in about 150 new donors.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Endowment funds intended uses (Part V, line 4)
Footnote for uncertain tax position under FIN 48 (Part X)
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Financial Accounting Standards Board has issued guidance on accounting for uncertainty in income taxes and Florida SouthWestern State College Foundation, Inc. has adopted this guidance. Florida SouthWestern State College Foundation, Inc. has evaluated its tax positions and any estimates utilized in its tax returns, and concluded that it has taken no uncertain tax positions that require adjustment to the financial statements to comply with the provisions of this guidance. Interest and penalties associated with uncertain tax positions will be recognized in income tax expense, if required.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990 governing body review Part VI line 11
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Form 990 is presented to the Board at the Finance Committee meeting and Board meeting for review and approval each year prior to filing.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Conflict of interest policy compliance Part VI line 12c
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Conflict of interest policy is reviewed and signed by all voting members of the Board each year.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: CEO executive director top management comp Part VI line 15a
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Foundation does not directly employ any individuals. Individuals are employed by the College. Compensation procedures are established by the College. Foundation reimburses the College for certain salaries.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Other officer or key employee compensation Part VI line 15b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Board Members are not compensated except for the President in his role as president. The Foundation does not directly employ any individuals. Individuals are employed by the College. Compensation procedures are established by the College. Foundation reimburses the College for certain salaries.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Governing documents etc available to public Part VI line 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: All policies are available upon request and on the Foundations website.
Part X, Line 25 Other Liabilities:Investments held until transfer from trust complete.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Part VII response or note to any other line in Part VII
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: 3 individuals listed on Part VII are officers of the Organizations, but were not voting members. 1 individual listed on Part VII was a former officer, but not a voting member. 1 individual listed on Part VII was a former director and not a voting member at the end of the year. For this reason, Part I and Part VI show 13 voting members.
William Banfield replaced Julia duPlooy as the Board of Trustee Representative starting in November 2022.
